{"key":"processedPost-12151673","value":{"id":12151673,"first":12149930,"last":12151673,"when":1267858062,"utime":"03/06/10 08:47 AM","content":"The agar boils over as the pressure cooker cools.&nbsp; The way to prevent this is to use much more water in the PC than normal, and instead of turning the stove off when time expires, turn it to its lowest setting.&nbsp; Allow it to lose pressure very slowly.<br /><br />The extra water provides thermal mass, which helps to keep the pressure up, allowing the agar to cool more slowly.<br /><br />Rather than a flask, I'd suggest a whiskey bottle with a tyvek filter and a hole in the lid as shown in this <a href=\"http://www.mushroomvideos.com/Agar-Petri-Dishes\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer noopener\">video clip</a> from my DVD.<br />RR","title":"Re: Agar splosion inside the Pressure Cooker","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}